 <H1>Summary (Contd.)</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Indexes must be chosen to speed up important queries (and perhaps some updates!).
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Index maintenance overhead on updates to key fields.
<LI>Choose indexes that can help many queries, if possible.
<LI>Build indexes to support index-only strategies.
<LI>Clustering is an important decision; only one index on a given relation can be clustered!
<LI>Order of fields in composite index key can be important.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Static indexes may have to be periodically re-built.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Statistics have to be periodically updated.</H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

